location.shield: Bridge Field, Dusty Bowl, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Outskirts, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

253.flavorText: If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it's a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain.

254.name: Cleffa

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

254.flavorText: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

255.name: Clefairy

location.sword: Giant's Cap, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Giant's Cap, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

255.flavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

256.name: Clefable

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

256.flavorText: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

257.name: Togepi

location.sword: Bridge FieldMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Bridge FieldMax Raid Battles

257.flavorText: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

258.name: Togetic

location.sword: Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

258.flavorText: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

259.name: Togekiss
259.evPoint: 2 Sp. Attack Point(s)1 Sp. Defense Point(s)

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

259.flavorText: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they've hardly been seen at all.

260.name: Munchlax

location.sword: Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

260.flavorText: Stuffing itself with vast amounts of food is its only concern. Whether the food is rotten or fresh, yummy or tastelessâit does not care.

261.name: Snorlax

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

261.flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

262.name: Cottonee

location.sword: Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

262.flavorText: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

263.name: Whimsicott

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

263.flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

264.name: Rhyhorn

location.sword: Route 8, Bridge Field, Giant's Cap, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 8, Bridge Field, Giant's Cap, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

264.flavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

265.name: Rhydon

location.sword: Route 10, Dusty Bowl, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 10, Dusty Bowl, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

265.flavorText: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

266.name: Rhyperior

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

266.flavorText: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

267.name: Gothita

location.sword: Giant's CapMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

267.flavorText: Though they're still only babies, there's psychic power stored in their ribbonlike feelers, and sometimes they use that power to fight.

268.name: Gothorita

location.sword: Dusty Bowl, Giant's CapMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

268.flavorText: It's said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokémon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.

269.name: Gothitelle

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

269.flavorText: It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It's also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.

270.name: Solosis

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Giant's CapMax Raid Battles

270.flavorText: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

271.name: Duosion

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Dusty BowlMax Raid Battles

271.flavorText: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mileâbut only if its two brains can agree with each other.

272.name: Reuniclus

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

272.flavorText: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokémon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.

273.name: Karrablast

location.sword: Route 7, Bridge Field, Giant's Cap, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 7, Bridge Field, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

273.flavorText: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

274.name: Escavalier

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Evolve Karrablast

274.flavorText: They use shells they've stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They're very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.

275.name: Shelmet

location.sword: Route 7, Bridge Field, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 7, Bridge Field, Giant's Cap, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

275.flavorText: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.

276.name: Accelgor

location.sword: Evolve Shelmet
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

276.flavorText: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

277.name: Elgyem

location.sword: Bridge Field, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Bridge Field, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

277.flavorText: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

278.name: Beheeyem

location.sword: Lake of OutrageStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Lake of OutrageStrong Spawn in Wild Area

278.flavorText: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

279.name: Cubchoo

location.sword: Route 10, Bridge Field, Dusty Bowl, Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke Hills, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 10, Bridge Field, Dusty Bowl, Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke Hills, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

279.flavorText: When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn't like.

280.name: Beartic

location.sword: Route 10Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 10Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

280.flavorText: It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.

281.name: Rufflet

location.sword: Route 8, Bridge Field, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

281.flavorText: If it spies a strong Pokémon, Rufflet can't resist challenging it to a battle. But if Rufflet loses, it starts bawling.

282.name: Braviary

location.sword: Dusty Bowl, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

282.flavorText: Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokémon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.

283.name: Vullaby

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Route 8, Bridge Field, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

283.flavorText: It wears a bone to protect its rear. It often squabbles with others of its kind over particularly comfy bones.

284.name: Mandibuzz

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Dusty Bowl, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

284.flavorText: Although it's a bit of a ruffian, this Pokémon will take lost Vullaby under its wing and care for them till they're ready to leave the nest.

285.name: Skorupi

location.sword: Route 6, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

285.flavorText: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

286.name: Drapion

location.sword: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

286.flavorText: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

287.name: Litwick

location.sword: Bridge Field, Motostoke RiverbankMotostoke GymMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Bridge Field, Motostoke RiverbankMotostoke GymMax Raid Battles

287.flavorText: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.

288.name: Lampent

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

288.flavorText: This Pokémon appears just before someone passes away, so it's feared as an emissary of death.

289.name: Chandelure

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

289.flavorText: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

290.name: Inkay

location.sword: Route 7, Route 9, Bridge Field, Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 7, Route 9, Bridge Field, Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles

290.flavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

291.name: Malamar

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

291.flavorText: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar's control.

292.name: Sneasel

location.sword: Route 8, Route 10, Bridge Field, Dusty Bowl, Giant's Cap, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 8, Route 10, Bridge Field, Dusty Bowl, Giant's Cap, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

292.flavorText: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

293.name: Weavile

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

293.flavorText: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.

294.name: Sableye

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Dusty BowlMax Raid Battles

294.flavorText: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.

295.name: Mawile

location.sword: Bridge Field, Dusty BowlMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

295.flavorText: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

296.name: Maractus

location.sword: Route 6, Bridge Field, Hammerlocke Hills, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Bridge Field, Hammerlocke Hills, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

296.flavorText: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

297.name: Sigilyph

location.sword: Lake of Outrage, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Lake of Outrage, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

297.flavorText: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians' emissaries.

298.name: Riolu

location.sword: Giant's CapMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Giant's CapMax Raid Battles

298.flavorText: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

299.name: Lucario

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

299.flavorText: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.

300.name: Torkoal

location.sword: Route 6, Giant's Cap, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Giant's Cap, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

300.flavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

301.name: Mimikyu

location.sword: Giant's MirrorMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Giant's MirrorMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

301.flavorText: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

302.name: Cufant

location.sword: Bridge FieldMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Bridge FieldMax Raid Battles

302.flavorText: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

303.name: Copperajah

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

303.flavorText: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

304.name: Qwilfish

location.sword: Route 9, Bridge Field, Dusty Bowl, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9, Bridge Field, Dusty Bowl, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

304.flavorText: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent's size.

305.name: Frillish

location.sword: Bridge Field, East Lake Axewell, Giant's Mirror, North Lake Miloch, West Lake AxewellMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Bridge Field, East Lake Axewell, Giant's Mirror, North Lake Miloch, West Lake AxewellMax Raid Battles

305.flavorText: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps, five miles below the ocean's surface.

306.name: Jellicent

location.sword: Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

306.flavorText: Most of this Pokémon's body composition is identical to sea water. It makes sunken ships its lair.

307.name: Mareanie

location.sword: Route 9, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9, Giant's Mirror, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

307.flavorText: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it's impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.

308.name: Toxapex

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9Max Raid Battles

308.flavorText: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokémon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.

309.name: Cramorant

location.sword: Route 9, Bridge Field, Lake of Outrage, Stony WildernessMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 9, Bridge Field, Lake of Outrage, Stony WildernessMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

309.flavorText: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

310.name: Toxel

location.sword: Route 7, Bridge Field, Giant's Cap, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 7, Bridge Field, Giant's Cap, Hammerlocke Hills, Motostoke Riverbank, Stony WildernessMax Raid Battles

310.flavorText: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

311.name: Toxtricity

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

311.flavorText: When this Pokémon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

312.name: Silicobra

location.sword: Route 6Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6Max Raid Battles

312.flavorText: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

313.name: Sandaconda

location.sword: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

313.flavorText: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

314.name: Hippopotas

location.sword: Route 6, Dusty BowlMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Dusty BowlMax Raid Battles

314.flavorText: It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.

315.name: Hippowdon

location.sword: Route 8, Giant's Mirror, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 8, Giant's Mirror, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

315.flavorText: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.

316.name: Durant

location.sword: Route 6, Giant's Mirror, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Giant's Mirror, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

316.flavorText: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.

317.name: Heatmor

location.sword: Route 6, Giant's Mirror, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Giant's Mirror, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

317.flavorText: There's a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

318.name: Helioptile

location.sword: Route 6, Giant's MirrorMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Giant's MirrorMax Raid Battles

318.flavorText: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon's electric moves.

319.name: Heliolisk

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

319.flavorText: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

320.name: Hawlucha

location.sword: Route 6, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 6, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

320.flavorText: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.

321.name: Trapinch

location.sword: Route 6Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles

321.flavorText: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.

322.name: Vibrava

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

322.flavorText: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.

323.name: Flygon

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

323.flavorText: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

324.name: Axew

location.sword: Route 6, Axew's Eye, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6, Axew's EyeMax Raid Battles

324.flavorText: These Pokémon nest in the ground and use their tusks to crush hard berries. Crushing berries is also how they test each other's strength.

325.name: Fraxure

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

325.flavorText: After battle, this Pokémon carefully sharpens its tusks on river rocks. It needs to take care of its tusksâif one breaks, it will never grow back.

326.name: Haxorus

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

326.flavorText: Its resilient tusks are its pride and joy. It licks up dirt to take in the minerals it needs to keep its tusks in top condition.

327.name: Yamask

location.sword: Route 6 (Galarian)Trade in Ballonlea (Unovan)Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 6Trade in Ballonlea (Unovan)Max Raid Battles

327.flavorText: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that's said to have been the face it had when it was still human.

328.name: Runerigus

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

328.flavorText: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

329.name: Cofagrigus

location.sword: Evolve Unovan Yamask
location.shield: Evolve Unovan Yamask

329.flavorText: This Pokémon has a body of sparkling gold. People say it no longer remembers that it was once human.

330.name: Honedge

location.sword: Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles

330.flavorText: Honedge's soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge's body.

331.name: Doublade

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

331.flavorText: Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.

332.name: Aegislash

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

332.flavorText: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.

333.name: Ponyta

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles

333.flavorText: It can't run properly when it's newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

334.name: Rapidash

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

334.flavorText: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

335.name: Sinistea

location.sword: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles

335.flavorText: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

336.name: Polteageist

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

336.flavorText: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

337.name: Indeedee

location.sword: Glimwood Tangle, Lake of Outrage (Male Only)Max Raid Battles (Male Only)
location.shield: Glimwood Tangle, Lake of Outrage (Female Only)Max Raid Battles (Female Only)

337.flavorText: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.

338.name: Phantump

location.sword: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles

338.flavorText: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit's rebirth as this Pokémon.

339.name: Trevenant

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

339.flavorText: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it's kind.

340.name: Morelull

location.sword: Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Giant's Mirror, Hammerlocke HillsMax Raid Battles

340.flavorText: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull's head. The caps regrow overnight.

341.name: Shiinotic

location.sword: Glimwood TangleMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Glimwood TangleMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

341.flavorText: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

342.name: Oranguru

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles

342.flavorText: With waves of its fanâmade from leaves and its own furâOranguru skillfully gives instructions to other Pokémon.

343.name: Passimian

location.sword: Glimwood TangleMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

343.flavorText: Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.

344.name: Morpeko

location.sword: Route 7, Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 7, Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

344.flavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.

345.name: Falinks

location.sword: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

345.flavorText: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

346.name: Drampa

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

346.flavorText: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

347.name: Turtonator

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

347.flavorText: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

348.name: Togedemaru

location.sword: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 8, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

348.flavorText: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

349.name: Snom

location.sword: Route 8, Route 10, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 8, Route 10, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

349.flavorText: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

350.name: Frosmoth

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

350.flavorText: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than ?290 degrees Fahrenheit.

351.name: Clobbopus

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9Max Raid Battles

351.flavorText: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

352.name: Grapploct

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

352.flavorText: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

353.name: Pincurchin

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9Max Raid Battles

353.flavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

354.name: Mantyke

location.sword: Route 9, Lake of Outrage, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9, Lake of Outrage, Motostoke RiverbankMax Raid Battles

354.flavorText: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhat sluggish. The colder waters of the seas in this region may be the cause.

355.name: Mantine

location.sword: Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

355.flavorText: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

356.name: Wailmer

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 9Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

356.flavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

357.name: Wailord

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9Max Raid Battles

357.flavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

358.name: Bergmite

location.sword: Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

358.flavorText: They chill the air around them to ?150 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing the water in the air into ice that they use as armor.

359.name: Avalugg

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

359.flavorText: At high latitudes, this Pokémon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

360.name: Dhelmise

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Route 9Max Raid Battles

360.flavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

361.name: Lapras

location.sword: Route 9Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 9Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

361.flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

362.name: Lunatone

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Route 8, Giant's CapMax Raid Battles

362.flavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It's active on the night of a full moon.

363.name: Solrock

location.sword: Route 8, Giant's CapMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

363.flavorText: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

364.name: Mime Jr.

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

364.flavorText: It mimics everyone it sees, but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.

365.name: Mr. Mime

location.shield: Route 10, Lake of Outrage (Galarian)Trade in Spikemuth (Kantonian)Max Raid Battles

365.flavorText: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidenceâmany scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

366.name: Mr. Rime

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

366.flavorText: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

367.name: Darumaka

location.sword: Route 8, Route 10Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

367.flavorText: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

368.name: Darmanitan

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

368.flavorText: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

369.name: Stonjourner

location.sword: Route 10, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

369.flavorText: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

370.name: Eiscue

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Route 10, Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

370.flavorText: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

371.name: Duraludon

location.sword: Route 10, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Route 10, Lake of OutrageMax Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

371.flavorText: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

372.name: Rotom

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

372.flavorText: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.

373.name: Ditto

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

373.flavorText: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

374.name: Dracozolt

location.sword: Revive Fossilized Bird & Fossilized Drake in Route 6
location.shield: Revive Fossilized Bird & Fossilized Drake in Route 6

374.flavorText: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

375.name: Arctozolt

location.sword: Revive Fossilized Bird & Fossilized Dino in Route 6
location.shield: Revive Fossilized Bird & Fossilized Dino in Route 6

375.flavorText: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

376.name: Dracovish

location.sword: Revive Fossilized Fish & Fossilized Drake in Route 6
location.shield: Revive Fossilized Fish & Fossilized Drake in Route 6

376.flavorText: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

377.name: Arctovish

location.sword: Revive Fossilized Fish & Fossilized Dino in Route 6
location.shield: Revive Fossilized Fish & Fossilized Dino in Route 6

377.flavorText: Though it's able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

378.name: Charmander

location.sword: Gift from Leon in PotswickMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Gift from Leon in PotswickMax Raid Battles

378.flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

379.name: Charmeleon

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

379.flavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

380.name: Charizard

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

380.flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

381.name: Type: Null

location.sword: Gift in Battle Tower
location.shield: Gift in Battle Tower

381.flavorText: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.

382.name: Silvally

location.sword: Evolve Type: Null
location.shield: Evolve Type: Null

382.flavorText: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

383.name: Larvitar

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

383.flavorText: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

384.name: Pupitar

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

384.flavorText: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

385.name: Tyranitar

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area

385.flavorText: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

386.name: Deino

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

386.flavorText: When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.

387.name: Zweilous

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

387.flavorText: While hunting for prey, Zweilous wanders its territory, its two heads often bickering over which way to go.

388.name: Hydreigon

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

388.flavorText: There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.

389.name: Goomy

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

389.flavorText: Because most of its body is water, it will dry up if the weather becomes too arid. It's considered the weakest dragon Pokémon.

390.name: Sliggoo

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

390.flavorText: Although this Pokémon isn't very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

391.name: Goodra

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

391.flavorText: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don't mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.

392.name: Jangmo-o

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

392.flavorText: They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together. The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

393.name: Hakamo-o

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Trade from Sword

393.flavorText: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body are signs of its strength. It shows them off to defeated opponents.

394.name: Kommo-o

location.sword: Max Raid BattlesStrong Spawn in Wild Area
location.shield: Trade from Sword

394.flavorText: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

395.name: Dreepy

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

395.flavorText: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

396.name: Drakloak

location.sword: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles
location.shield: Lake of OutrageMax Raid Battles

396.flavorText: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

397.name: Dragapult

location.sword: Max Raid Battles
location.shield: Max Raid Battles

397.flavorText: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

398.name: Zacian

location.sword: Energy Plant
location.shield: Trade from Sword

398.flavorText: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

399.name: Zamazenta

location.sword: Trade from Shield
location.shield: Energy Plant

399.flavorText: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

400.name: Eternatus

location.sword: Energy Plant
location.shield: Energy Plant

400.flavorText: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.
